                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9783: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="85" xml:id="d547fn85">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-30T18:35:00+08:00"
                            >August 30, 1937—6:35 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 30—8:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0030. It is my intention unless otherwise directed to notify the Japanese Admiral
                    that under existing conditions I cannot recognize the right of Japanese
                    men-of-war to stop and search United States merchant vessels and that I shall
                    instruct the vessels of my command accordingly.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
